  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community Based Advocacy  for Access, Gender Equality and Reduced Stigma</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">7.2% of Uganda&#x2019;s population is living with HIV and the rate has been rising since 2006. People with HIV still experience stigma and this marginalisation is one of the main reasons they are not able to access services. This project strengthens and expands the work of two community-based organisations, establishing and supporting a wider network of support groups of people living with HIV. There are close links with government clinics to improve the quality and availability of HIV services. It also helps establish village savings and loan schemes and helps create and strengthen opportunities for project beneficiaries to make a living. The project aims to improve the lives of people living with HIV, and make them more accepted in their communities.</narrative>
  </description>
